From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: hotdog local experiment <hotdog-local@example.invalid>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: advertise Android-style Image text offset

Android/Lineage boot images for hotdog carry an ARM64 Image header with
text_offset set to 0x80000.  Mainline arm64 currently writes zero here,
which is valid for recent bootloaders but differs from the downstream
Android-style header this experiment is trying to match.

This patch is intentionally local/experimental.  It only changes the
advertised Image header field; the boot image load address remains owned
by deviceinfo/mkbootimg.
---
 arch/arm64/kernel/head.S | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/kernel/head.S b/arch/arm64/kernel/head.S
index 007129adfc3c..5dbb49444af1 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/kernel/head.S
+++ b/arch/arm64/kernel/head.S
@@ -61,7 +61,7 @@
 	 */
 	efi_signature_nop			// special NOP to identity as PE/COFF executable
 	b	primary_entry			// branch to kernel start, magic
-	.quad	0				// Image load offset from start of RAM, little-endian
+	.quad	0x00080000			// Image load offset from start of RAM, little-endian
 	le64sym	_kernel_size_le			// Effective size of kernel image, little-endian
 	le64sym	_kernel_flags_le		// Informative flags, little-endian
 	.quad	0				// reserved
-- 
2.50.0

